--------------------------------------------------------
Configure Global Git parameters
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git config --global user.email "krohith@clemson.edu"
$ git config --global user.name "Rohith Krishnan"

--------------------------------------------------------
Git Help
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git help <command>
$ git <command> --help

--------------------------------------------------------
Start/Stop Tracking a project
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git init
$ rm -rf .git

--------------------------------------------------------
Check status
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git status

--------------------------------------------------------
Add files to be ignored in ".gitignore" text file
--------------------------------------------------------

$ touch .gitignore

--------------------------------------------------------
Add/remove files to Staging Area
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git add -A
$ git add <filename>

$ git reset 
$ git reset <filename>

--------------------------------------------------------
Commit files from Staging Area to Repository
--------------------------------------------------------

$ git commit -m "<message>"
$ git commit

--------------------------------------------------------
Remote Repository
--------------------------------------------------------

# info about the remote repo
$ git remote -v

# lists all the branches
$ git branch -a

# difference in the code
$ git diff

# status of your files
$ git status 

--------------------------------------------------------
ALWAYS DO THIS BEFORE UPDATING THE REPO
--------------------------------------------------------
$ git pull origin master
$ git push origin master

--------------------------------------------------------
Create Branches for desired features
--------------------------------------------------------
'*' indicates the current working branch 

# list all the branches
$ git branch

# create a local branch
$ git branch <branch_name>

# work on a branch
$ git checkout <branch_name>

# push branch to repo
$ git add -A
$ git commit -m "<message>"
$ git push -u origin <branch_name>

# merge the branch to master branch
$ git checkout master
$ git pull origin master
$ git merge <branch_name>
$ git push origin master
